Answer.feedback: I get that the 'right' answers are basically maximizing the benefits while spreading them out (I think). So like in the travel times scenario, 1: 1/101/1, 2: 1/1/101, 3:1/51/51. All three are equal gains overall but 3 is probably the best given it distributes it more. But say the medical costs one... 1: 51/1/101, 2:101/51/1, 3: 1/51/1. Surely it's not 3, but how would I choose between 1 or 2? Unless the idea is just that either answer is fine, in which case, never mind all this text.
